===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[exercise]] the rational faculty; to [[deduce]] [[inference]]s from [[premise]]s; to perform the process of [[deduction]] or of [[induction]]; to [[ratiocinate]]; to reach [[conclusion]]s by a systematic comparison of facts.
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} Hence: To carry on a process of deduction or of induction, in order to [[convince]] or to [[confute]]; to [[formulate]] and set forth [[proposition]]s and the inferences from them; to [[argue]].
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[converse]]; to compare [[opinion]]s.
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To arrange and present the reasons for or against; to [[examine]] or [[discuss]] by arguments; to [[debate]] or discuss.
#: ''I '''reasoned''' the matter with my friend.''
# {{lb|en|transitive|rare}} To support with reasons, as a [[request]].
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[persuade]] by reasoning or argument.
#: ''to '''reason''' one into a belief; to '''reason''' one out of his plan''
# {{lb|en|transitive|with ''[[down]]''}} To [[overcome]] or [[conquer]] by [[adduce|adducing]] reasons.
#: ''to '''reason''' down a passion''
# {{lb|en|transitive|usually with ''[[out]]''}} To find by [[logical]] [[process]]; to [[explain]] or [[justify]] by reason or argument.
#: ''to '''reason''' out the causes of the librations of the moon'''''

